-- DKSH Shareholders Sell Stake Valued at $333 Million, Terms Show
-- B y   F r a n c e s c a   C i n e l l i   a n d   R u t h   D a v i d
-- 2013-04-25T10:03:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-24/dksh-shareholders-selling-stake-worth-217-5-million-terms-show.html
DKSH Holding AG (DKSH) , which advises and
helps businesses grow in Asia, is selling 4 million shares,
valuing the stake at about 314 million Swiss francs ($333
million), according to terms obtained by  Bloomberg News .  The deal size was raised to 4 million shares from 2.5
million today, the terms show. The sale values the stake at 314
million francs based on a price of 78.5 francs a share, and
orders below that price won’t be considered. DKSH shares fell 4
percent to 79.15 francs at 11:50 am in Zurich, where the company
is based.  UBS AG and  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  are managing the sale.
The shares were initially offered in a range of 78 Swiss francs
to market price, terms from yesterday show.  “Certain strategic investors” and DKSH management are
selling stakes as part of the transaction, according to terms.  Secondary share sales including block deals in  Europe , the
Middle East and Africa have raised $31 billion this year, an
increase of about 60 percent from the same period in 2012,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporters on this story:
